   <content type="html">&lt;p&gt;In this short guide I&amp;#39;ll explain how I built my own desktop weather display on an &lt;a href=&quot;http://arduino.cc/en/Main/ArduinoBoardUno&quot;&gt;Arduino Uno&lt;/a&gt; running Node and &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/rwaldron/johnny-five&quot;&gt;Johnny-Five&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;hr&gt;

&lt;p&gt;You&amp;#39;ll need the following things before starting:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A 16x2 LCD display, I used the &lt;a href=&quot;http://arduino.cc/documents/datasheets/LCD-WH1602B-TMI.pdf&quot;&gt;LCD-WH1602B&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;An Arduino board, many will work with this project, but I used an &lt;a href=&quot;http://arduino.cc/en/Main/ArduinoBoardUno&quot;&gt;Arduino Uno&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Different coloured jumper wires&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A potentiometer&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

